> Greetings to you who have contributed to the mpg123 project in some way and who I was able to get the eMail address from!
>
> I, Thomas Orgis, am taking over active maintainership of the project from Michael Hipp.
> To successfully sustain this project outside the hands of the caring original author, I feel urged to have a clear license statement.
> I also want to regain some "territory" like the free software section of a distribution for mpg123 that it lost/never had because of it's freeness being unclear in certain terms.
>
> Michael already announced to release mpg123 under the GPL and the extracted mpglib under LPGL (what he then did).
>
> It is desirable to have _one_ license for all of mpg123 to make further development and restructuring possible.
> Thus, meeting both the requirements of freeness and sustainability of current uses of mpglib the decision was made to use the GNU Lesser General Public License, Version 2.1, for the whole package.
>
> I plan to release an updated version with the LGPL license statements in the following weeks and kindly ask everyone who has contributed code and is not agreeing with this to contact me to settle the issue.
>
> Replies indicating that there are _no_ issues with a LPGL release are highly appreciated!
>
